undation\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"color\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"texture\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"counter_melody\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"accent\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"punctuation\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\")`.\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\n+**Tests:** `tests/test_cast_planner.py` (5 tests, all assert on `list[str]`).\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\n+## `SampleSelector`\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\n+**Does not exist yet.** Confirmed by:\\\\\\\\n+- `grep \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"class SampleSelector\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"` → no matches in any `.py` file.\\\\\\\\n+- No `sample_library.py` or `sample_selector.py` in `my-claw/tools/senseweave/` (existing sampler modules are `sample_dsp_activity.py`, `sample_event_renderer.py`, `sample_lab.py`, `sample_status.py`, `sampler_buffers.py`, `sampler_dispatch.py`, `sampler_scheduler.py` — none expose a selector class).\\\\\\\\n+- `sdp/implementation-plan.md:66` — **T-028** is the task to *implement* `SampleSelector`. Per `sdp/implementation-plan.md:47`, T-016 itself depends on T-011 only, but the wiring assumes a forthcoming `SampleSelector` API.\\\\\\\\n+- `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-architecture.md:194` describes it as \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"mode/arc/mood-aware deterministic picker\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" returning a `SampleRecord` from a `SampleLibrary`.\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\n+**Implication:** T-016 cannot literally wire an existing `SampleSelector` — it must either (a) wait on T-028, or (b) define the integration seam (a Protocol or callable hook on `select_cast_ids`) that T-028 plugs into, plus stub-friendly tests. **Recommend escalating** to clarify ordering vs. T-028.\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\n+## Current cast-metadata construction\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\n+**File:** `my-claw/tools/duet_composer.py:382-402` — sole caller of `select_cast_ids`.\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\n+Lines 390-396:\\\\\\\\n+```python\\\\\\\\n+cast_ids = select_cast_ids(\\\\\\\\n+    all_chars,\\\\\\\\n+    _cast_history,\\\\\\\\n+    mood_energy=mood_energy,\\\\\\\\n+    max_chars=max_chars,\\\\\\\\n+)\\\\\\\\n+cast = [{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": cid, **all_chars[cid][\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"voice\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"], \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"char_name\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": cid} for cid in cast_ids]\\\\\\\\n+```\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\n+The cast-dict shape (per element) is built **at the call site, not inside `select_cast_ids`**:\\\\\\\\n+- `id`: character id\\\\\\\\n+- `char_name`: same id (duplicated)\\\\\\\\n+- spread of `all_chars[cid][\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"voice\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"]`, which carries: `synth`, `role`, `register` (`[lo_midi, hi_midi]`), `params` (dict: `attack`, `release`, `verb`, `dly`, plus synth-specific knobs) — fields exercised by `_play_character` at `duet_composer.py:404-429`.\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\n+History bookkeeping at lines 399-400: `_cast_history` is updated to a flat list of ids, capped at 60.\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\n+## Where to extend for T-016\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\n+To attach a pre-selected sample per piece when the cast contains `sw_sampler`, two seams are plausible:\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\n+1. **Caller-side (smaller change):** in `duet_composer._get_cast`, after the list-comp at line 396, run a `SampleSelector` over cast members whose `synth == \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"sw_sampler\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"` and merge a `sample` (`SampleRecord`-ish dict) field into that cast entry. `select_cast_ids` keeps its `list[str]` contract.\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\n+2. **Planner-side (richer contract change):** add an optional `sample_selector: SampleSelector | None = None` kwarg to `select_cast_ids` and change the return type to `list[CastEntry]` (TypedDict with `id`, `voice`, optional `sample: SampleRecord`). This breaks the current `list[str]` contract and ripples into `duet_composer.py:399` (`_cast_history` extraction) and `tests/test_cast_planner.py` (5 assertions on string lists).\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\n+Option **(1)** is the smaller change and matches the \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"smallest change that satisfies the task\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" rule. Option (2) better matches the PRD framing (\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"attached to the cast metadata\\\\\\\\\\