st slice\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" described in the LEAD agent's commit message. While the full `BufferPool` and LRU eviction (part of the larger T-001 in the new plan) are deferred to later sub-tasks, the specific \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Task\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" defined in the verify prompt was fulfilled.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nHowever, there is a significant **Completeness** issue regarding the repository state:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- The LEAD agent modified the PRD (`sdp/prd-snapshot.md`), Implementation Plan (`sdp/implementation-plan.md`), and Task Graph (`sdp/task-graph.md`) in the worktree to reflect the new \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Sampler\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" project, but **did not commit these changes**. \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- This leaves the repository in an inconsistent state where the code reflects the Sampler PRD, but the committed documentation still reflects the old Humanization PRD.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Consistency\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe implementation is consistent with the Sampler backend's OSC requirements. The use of `wave` for header parsing is appropriate for T1. \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Security\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nNo security vulnerabilities or secret leaks were identified. Path handling uses `pathlib` safely.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Quality\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe code is clean, well-commented, and includes a comprehensive test suite (`tests/test_sampler_buffers.py`) that covers edge cases like stereo files and missing WAVs. The tests use a clean mock OSC client.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Issues Found\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- [ ] **Minor — Redundant OSC Command**: `/b_alloc` is technically redundant when followed by `/b_allocRead`, as the latter performs allocation. However, this follows the literal wording of the spec and is not harmful.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- [ ] **Minor — Uncommitted PRD/Plan Updates**: The LEAD agent left the Sampler PRD and plan updates unstaged/uncommitted in the worktree, leading to an inconsistent repository state.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- [ ] **Minor — Worktree Clutter**: Unrelated syncopation changes in `music_tracker.py` and `groove_engine.py` were left unstaged in the worktree.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Verdict: PASS WITH NOTES\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Notes for Lead Agent\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n1. The implementation of `on_sampler_load` is correct and well-tested.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n2. **CRITICAL:** You must commit the PRD, Implementation Plan, and Task Graph updates that you have in your worktree. The current `HEAD` still shows the old Humanization plan while the code is for the Sampler plan.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n3. Please clean up or commit the unrelated syncopation and phase-offset changes in `music_tracker.py` and `groove_engine.py`.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n4. Hardening check: Confirmed that `bootstrap_identity()` is already correctly wired in both `daemon.py` and `cypherclaw_daemon.py` before `FirstBootAnnouncer`.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"file_path\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"sdp/verification/t-001@20260425t183959za-verify.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}}\\\\\\\\n++./sdp/runner.log:2198:│ Verify  agent=gemini  time=2m 17s                                                                                                                                                                    │\\\\\\\\n++./sdp/runner.log:2232:│ Verify: gemini  google/gemini/3-flash-preview (standard)                                                                                                                                             │\\\\\\\\n++./sdp/runner.log:2365:[STATE] Verifying — Verifier gemini is reviewing output.\\\\\\\\n++./sdp/runner.log:2372:│ label=Verify: T-001@20260425T183959Zb                                                                                                                                                                │\\\\\\\\n++./sdp/runner.log:2376:{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\