ns |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 5 | T-005 | Encode SenseWeave voice-to-music interpretation rules. | T1 | 2 | 3 | MPC-014 | — | - room, membrane/contact mic, garden, Theramini, archive, and network sources have musical mappings for pitch, rhythm, density, harmony, timbre, mix, and deference<br/>- Perform-VE condenser/room mic fallback is represented as a source option<br/>- tests verify quiet/noisy room, rain/wind/contact vibration, garden inactivity, Theramini activity, archive recall, and network/weather mappings |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 6 | T-006 | Implement ensemble-space and Theramini partner behavior from the course. | T1 | 3 | 3 | MPC-015 | — | - policy supports listening first, complementary register, rhythmic sympathy, harmonic response intervals, accompaniment textures, call/response, imitation, commentary, completion, and silence<br/>- score/tracker metadata identifies current lead/support roles<br/>- tests verify no register crowding, no excessive overlap during human/Theramini gesture, and recovery to solo mode |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 7 | T-007 | Add a genre-literacy strategy library. | T1 | 2 | 3 | MPC-016 | — | - strategies exist for ambient/drone/generative, minimalism, jazz, IDM/electronic, classical/orchestral form, musique concrete/electroacoustic, spectral music, blues, world-music concepts, and post-rock/experimental builds<br/>- strategies can influence form, harmony, rhythm, synthesis, arrangement, and mix without hardcoding imitation<br/>- tests verify strategy selection, arc affinity, and no missing required genre strategy |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 8 | T-008 | Make the 30-minute production score executable. | T1 | 2 | 3 | MPC-017 | — | - procedural arc exposes per-phase density, dynamic, harmonic, rhythm, timbre, spatial, compression, SenseWeave, and synthesis targets<br/>- score-tree commissioning and tracker compilation use those targets for long pieces and 5-minute proxy tests<br/>- tests verify