+### 7. Deniable Asset Bus
 
+The Deniable Asset Bus is a filesystem handoff between a requester writing
+`requests/<request_id>.json` and the CypherClaw producer writing assets plus
+`deliverables/<request_id>.result.json`. Renderer dispatch goes through the
+`BoxRunner` protocol so producer code can use `FakeBoxRunner` in tests and
+`SSHBoxRunner` in production.
+
+`SSHBoxRunner` keeps request-derived strings out of shell command lines. The
+local `ssh` invocation is an argv list that calls the fixed
+`promptclaw.asset_bus.remote_exec` helper; the renderer argv is JSON stdin, and
+the remote helper launches the renderer as an argv list with `shell=False`.
+Generated files are pulled back from the remote run directory with an argv-list
+`rsync` transfer and returned as local `BoxRunResult.artifacts`.
+
